en_102493_0	Venerable Buddhist Monks at the Gangaaraama Meditation Centre in Mukkama in Katana North charge that a group including former Chief Justice Sarath N. Silva came to the centre and felled trees without permission.
en_102493_1	Meditation Centre Rector Venerable Kosgoda Samatha-seela Thero told our news team that he had lodged a complaint about this at the police.
en_102493_2	Our news team inquired about this from former Chief Justice Sarath N. Silva as well.
en_102493_3	The former Chief Justice said that the land accommodating the Meditation Centre belonged to him.
